name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Every time I walk into a classroom I get excited for the road ahead. Our kids are smart, kind and full of excitement, and they deserve the brightest future.   Let's give them the best head start by investing early through universal pre-K. It's the right thing to do.  https://t.co/oPfH7KvvGg

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Investing in our education system is investing in the future of our kids and our workforce. Universal pre-K will help our students succeed and addresses workforce challenges by helping our families. It's a win for our kids and our economy.

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: This is my friend, Boone, and we are celebrating him on #WorldDownSyndromeDay. He is a special boy who makes the world a much better place.  https://t.co/2B613dbZdK

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: My thoughts and prayers are with the family and loved ones of Cpl. Jacob Moore of Catlettsburg, Kentucky. We are grateful for his service and extend our condolences to all those impacted.  ^JC

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: The Kentuckians sitting in our classrooms today aren't future leaders – they're leaders now. Organizations like @KYStuVoiceTeam are allowing our youth to make their voice heard to bring positive change and I am always impressed by what I see.  https://t.co/PAIamMBAE9

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: As a rural Kentuckian, I am committed to ensuring the economic momentum we're seeing reaches every community. Team Kentucky is making progress and that was clear this week as @GovAndyBeshear cut the ribbon on the first build-ready site in Johnson County!

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: One in three Kentuckians depend on Medicaid, and Team Kentucky is committed to ensuring this program continues to provide access to affordable care for more of our people.

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Proud to cheer on @RacersHoops tonight in the @NCAA tournament! Good luck.  https://t.co/GbsrUMxG31

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Jefferson Elementary in @HendersonSchool is set to be the safest school in the state as the first to feature a school tornado shelter. I can't wait to see the difference this investment makes when these doors open in August!    https://t.co/ScWIz1DXv0

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Welcome home, @CoachKennyPayne! We are excited to have you back in Louisville, leading the @LouisvilleMBB program.

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: #TeamKentucky has lost a health care hero, selfless servant and friend. Dr. Hartlage led the COVID-19 vaccine rollout in Louisville and her leadership helped to save countless lives. Our thoughts are with her family, friends, and colleagues.   https://t.co/AaoZzY7Ha8

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: The importance of high-quality child care cannot be overstated. Our communities, our workforce, our economy and our families depend on it. It's high time we invest in these educators and our littlest learners – and that is what #TeamKentucky continues to work for.  https://t.co/KhIXIyYtVl

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Believe it or not, this was my first time donating blood.  @KyRedCross made me comfortable and made the entire process quick and easy.  We're facing a blood shortage and we need more people to donate. Take the step – it's worth it. Together, we can make a difference.  https://t.co/n9bEApuoXs

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: High-speed internet is essential for our students, educators and every Kentuckian. Our administration is working to expand access so that every community in our commonwealth has the same opportunities.

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: I want to wish all of the teams across the commonwealth entering the @NCAA Tournament the best of luck! All of #TeamKentucky is cheering you on. #MarchMadness

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Each week we're sharing more and more positive news for Kentuckians. Tune in today at 12:30 p.m. EDT for the latest on new jobs, infrastructure investments and more.

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Team Kentucky is working daily to ensure the prosperity we're seeing from our economic growth reaches every corner of the commonwealth. As a rural Kentuckian, I know the impact these investments can have on our families and in our communities.  https://t.co/dogzYnOjXX

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Thank you to @NCHSCardinals for stopping by the Capitol to say hello! It's so nice having students back for visits again.  https://t.co/GDL3P5E8PI

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Our administration is committed to helping all Kentucky businesses – big and small – thrive. Thank you to the Radcliff Small Business Alliance for inviting me to discuss the investments we're making today to ensure success in the future.  https://t.co/OKC0KLPxjn

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: There are so many remarkable Kentuckians who step up daily to volunteer and make a difference across our commonwealth. I visited @voamid today in Louisville to thank some of these heroes for their work and the impact they make in our communities.  https://t.co/biGFVGOoOW

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Today @GovAndyBeshear once again did what's right for the people of Kentucky. It's simply not right to take away services our people depend on. We've got to push politics aside and do what's best for Kentuckians.

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: It was great to be in Louisville this morning for the @KYGOEC annual conference. Our priority is to invest in Kentucky's children early, ensuring a bright future for them and for our commonwealth.  https://t.co/Q2YXyUwEbY

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: We've come a long way, Kentucky! But the key to maintaining this progress is up to us. Make sure you get vaccinated and boosted, and stay home when sick. #TogetherKy

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Delivering clean water is a priority for Team Kentucky, because it helps our people live better lives and our communities grow. I was proud to award $2.7 million to Grayson, Breckinridge and Meade counties today through @GovAndyBeshear's Cleaner Water Program.  https://t.co/4A8QSqHfSd

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Lt. Gov. Jacqueline Coleman awarded $2,771,935 in funding to Breckenridge, Grayson and Meade counties. The funding comes through @GovAndyBeshear's Cleaner Water Program.   Read more:  https://t.co/Z1JyIFQLaT  https://t.co/4tV1X8moXg

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Our student athletes are making an impact, not just on the court, but in our communities. I am glad they saw we have their back last week with the signing of the name, image and likeness bill. We are lucky to have them in Kentucky.

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: When we don’t invest in our infrastructure, our people and our communities suffer. We need funding to ensure projects like the Brent Spence Bridge companion bridge happen.

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: We've come a long way, Kentucky. Tune in today to hear about the progress we've made, how to stay vigilant and what reporting will look like going forward.

name: Lt. Governor Jacqueline Coleman
tweet: Today is the deadline for families in Western Kentucky to apply for @FEMA assistance. Please visit  https://t.co/B73V9II9Kx, use the FEMA app or call the helpline at 800-621-3362.
